-- NBC Names Don Nash to Replace Bell as ‘Today’ Executive Producer
-- B y   A l e x   S h e r m a n
-- 2012-11-14T20:48:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-14/nbc-names-don-nash-to-replace-bell-as-today-executive-producer.html
NBC Universal  said Don Nash will
replace Jim Bell as executive producer of the “Today” show
effective Dec. 1.  Nash has been with “Today” for 23 years and has served as
the show’s senior broadcast producer for the past seven, New
York-based NBC Universal said today in a statement. He will
report to Alexandra Wallace, who will oversee all four hours of
the show as executive in charge.  NBC, majority owned by  Comcast Corp. (CMCSA) , announced yesterday
it is shifting Bell to full-time executive producer of its
Olympics coverage.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Sherman in New York at 
